{this is weird: stable_sum(H,phi_H) is a sum of parameters P_H
viewed as irreducibles this is not necessarily stable
viewed as standards this is stable: is_stable_std(P)=true
so, take CP_H=composition_series(P_H): this is a stable sum of irreducibles
so we can apply epstar_stable(CP_H,G,z): giving a sum of irreducibles,
 then its character_formula is a sum of standards}
set epstar_stable_std_old(L_homomorphism phi_H,RealForm G,ratvec z)=ParamPol:
let H=dual_quasisplit_form(inner_class(phi_H)) then
P_H=stable_sum_std(H,phi_H) then
CP_H=composition_series(P_H) then
ep_irr=epstar_stable(CP_H,G,z) then
ep_std=character_formula(ep_irr) in
ep_std

